Working with celebrities has always been great for my photography career but it’s not as glamorous as some might imagine. Did you know sometimes you only get 3 to 5 minutes to photograph a celebrity ?
Depending on their schedule and their handlers the photo shoot can go super quick  Often times I’ve had to come a few hours ahead of time, set up and test my lighting and be ready for that “moment” they arrive & jump in front of my camera before moving on to the thousand other things they have to do that day. It’s short , fast and you need to be ON POINT.  My favorite celebrity that I’ve photographed had to be @aliciakeys  She was warm , sweet & amazing. Do what you love and you’ll never have to work another day in your life!!

Yesterday was a very special day for The Xeron family. Our precious angel Elektra Zoe was baptized in the Greek Orthodox Church (St. George in Bethesda , MD) It’s the very same church that I was baptized over 52 years ago!
We were surrounded by immediate family only (50 plus ppl) Greeks have BIG families lol
The Godparents my sister in-law Paraskevi Evelyn Xeron and her son (my nephew) Dimitri Xeron. I am so honored to have them make a lifelong commitment in front of God. It makes me and Chelsea Xeron sleep better at night knowing that our babies will be in the best of hands in the event of any tradgedy (fingers crossed we never need to cash in these chips)
I feel like the luckiest man alive to have a wife as caring, loving and GORGEOUS as Chelsea. And both go my children are truly the greatest blessing of my entire life. (niko & Baby Elektra

Hello everybody old and new followers.
My name is Drew Xeron , Fashion, Commercial, portrait , lifestyle ,editorial and headshot photographer. I am a native of Washington DC and 99.3% Greek (according to 23 and me) I married the love of my life Chelsea Xeron, and together we made 2 gorgeous children Niko age 4 and Elektra currently 11 months old.  We also have 2 twin Shih Tzu dogs (Wolfy & Chewy) Aside from being a photographer for hire I also own @studio52dc with my wife & business partner @chelseaxeron  if you need an experienced photographer that understands your needs , I’m your guy!
I have a Studio located within our event venue in Northeast Washington DC’s Ivy City neighborhood. I’ve been lucky enough to be published in some of the largest international magazines in the world. British Vogue , GW, Essence to name a few .  I also have a full service video production company.  And if you ever need a space to host your next special event. (milestone birthdays, weddings, bar mitzvahs, corporate, holiday party, etc..) please check out @studio52dc please don’t hesitate to reach out in the comments or even slide into my DM’s, if you need anything relating to Photography, video production, special event venue, or even just to say hello! #dcphotographer #marylandphotographer #dmvphotographer #bestphotographer #art #dcphotoshoot #celebrityphotographer #instagram #photographersofinstagram #virginiaphotographer #dancephotographer  #nycphotogtapher #laphotographer

New work Posted @withregram • @imsimplywinter The significance and essence of who you are always shows up in crisis, chaos, or change.  At those moments, you either sink or soar.  I’m grateful to God that I’ve never encountered a Red Sea he didn’t part or an ocean I couldn’t swim in.  Today is 4/11 and while that may not be significant to many, it is to me.  It felt like the right day to encourage someone to be grateful for their past regardless of what they’ve been through.  Don’t get hung up on what isn’t or what was.  Keep putting in the work & moving forward.  Your past creates the path to greatness!

This one was very special!!! so happy and blessed to be a part of this journey with this amazing couple  @jenniferlucytyler Posted @withregram • @jenniferlucytyler This is for those who have lost hope. This is for those whose prayers have gone unanswered year after year. 

I am no faith hero. I didn’t “manifest” this. I didn’t prophesy this. And at one point I stopped believing it would happen for us. Trust me when I say, being a first time mom at 41 wasn’t on my “vision board” when we married over 11 years ago. My dreams of motherhood fell apart in my heart with every miscarriage, and every month my period would arrive. 

This is a miracle only God could have granted because of His will, His timing and ultimate plan. This is the timing for our lives, and for her life. He was aware of this before the foundations of the world 🌎. This is His mercy and lovingkindness in spite of me. He is bigger than the diagnosis of “unexplained infertility.”

He receives every bit of glory for the beautiful gift we are birthing. IVF was the avenue, but again, He gets the glory because all life comes from God.

I will say, it matters who you marry. Even when I lost hope, Jeff never did. He always saw this. It didn’t matter my age, or how it was going to happen. He knew it would. Thank you baby🙏🏾 for never losing hope in our future even when I did.
